text: Kobilja Glava is a village in Vogošća municipality, Sarajevo Canton, near city of Sarajevo. ==Population== ===Ethnic composition, 1991 census=== total: 2,866 *Bosniaks - 2,750 (95.95%) *Serbs - 46 (1.60%) *"Yugoslavs" - 37 (1.29%) *Croats - 4 (0.13%) *others and unknown - 29 (1.01%) Mjesna zajednica Kobilja Glava The local community Kobilja Glava is part of the municipality Vogošća which includes: Streets: \- Ulica Kobilja Glava, \- Ulica Bušća, \- Ulica Novi rezervoar, \- Ulica Slatinski put, \- Ulica Stara cesta Jezera, \- Ulica Stara cesta I, \- Dio ulice Šipska, \- Ulica Ejuba Delalića, \- Naseljeno mjesto Grahovište. ==See also== * Vogošća ==References== *Official results from the book: Ethnic composition of Bosnia-Herzegovina population, by municipalities and settlements, 1991. census, Zavod za statistiku Bosne i Hercegovine - Bilten no.234, Sarajevo 1991. ==External links== *facebook page *YouTube video Category:Villages in the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina Category:Vogošća Category:Populated places in Vogošća
